Impress.js is a JavaScript library that works in conjunction with HTML & CSS
-> highly customizable

html file. data-x, data-y attributes change the position of the content.

data-z attributes change the closeness of the elements along the z axis.

data-scale attribute - scales content making slides appear bigger or smaller

data-rotate - rotates slides by anumber of degrees in 2D

data-rotate-x, data-rotate-y, data-rotate-z allow us to rotate slides in 3 dimensions.  show robotics slide of 3d roations

Older browsers do not support impress js



http://www.1stwebdesigner.com/creating-stunning-visualizations-with-impress-js/#/slide1

Impress.js is a jQuery plugin created on github by bartez which uses CSS3 functionality to create presentations. All the modern browsers will support the stunning visualizations created by Impress.js.


http://www.andismith.com/blog/2012/01/impress-with-impress/
active slides and hiding unactive slides
.step {
  opacity:0.2;
}

.step.active {
  opacity: 1;
}


Linking to a slide
For example, a slide with an ID of "statistics" will be accessible by appending "#/statistics" to the end of the URL.


overview slide
<div id="overview" class="step" data-x="600" data-y="300" data-scale="2"></div>

.step-overview .step {
  opacity: 1;
  cursor: pointer;
}


